description:
src/server.rs:213-217 — webfinger handler uses an if-let-else for early return:

    let acct = if let Some(acct) = query.resource.strip_prefix(prefix) {
        acct
    } else {
        return (StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST, ...).into_response();
    };

This is the exact pattern that let-else (stabilized in Rust 1.65, well within MSRV 1.80) was designed for:

    let Some(acct) = query.resource.strip_prefix(prefix) else {
        return (StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST, ...).into_response();
    };

Same pattern appears at line 220-222 with split_once.

Impact: Readability. let-else is the idiomatic way to express 'unwrap or return early' in modern Rust.
